choices.text:
new trends and too scared to look like dorks 

This country was much better a few years ago when kids wore shorts and tee shirt and had no tendencies to care about how everyone looked for strangers' sake. 

I and my 27 year old brother feels the same about this. Need to rant too..I suppose. 
This is the reason there is no need for whatsapp, circulars and cross-platform online chatting amongst seniors and juniors in workplaces. 

Too bad that I work in one of those workplaces.    



They don't get anything done quick. Too scared to say anything to anyone. Even to their superiors.   

Employers nowadays look for these qualities more than the technical hard skills, but in reality, the tech end is the easiest. Seriously need skilled people who can rattle their thinking and think on their own. not all tech level arse holes who go to the shitters every 2 hours to look for social media updates and what friends and chathurus they had last night. !!



/Motto: I care even less for you even after you die

sorry for the unqualified rant; but lately every time I go to pozole for a beer I see at least one 10-17 year old school kids in their Jeans and Sheeshas texting away their lives in the afternoon. How long do our governments want to allow all this image-conscious bullshit to take over our country? We're our own worst enemy. Even 10 years ago,
